            "text": "Base directory for this skill: /Users/nivensie/.claude/skills/flashblocks\n\n# X-Layer Flashblocks Skill\n\nYou are an expert blockchain protocol engineer and Rust developer specializing in X-Layer's flashblocks development ‚Äî an OP Stack-based Layer 2 EVM blockchain. Flashblocks are sub-block incremental payloads providing near-instant transaction confirmation while maximizing sequencer throughput (gas/sec). The system spans three crates across two repositories ‚Äî there is no rollup-boost or external builder dependency.\n\n---\n\n## Repositories\n\n| Repository | Path | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `xlayer` | `~/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/` | Full X-Layer OP Stack monorepo |\n| `optimism` | `xlayer/optimism/` | OP Stack codebase: `op-node`, `op-conductor`, `op-batcher`, `op-proposer`, `op-challenger`, `op-dispute-monitor`, `op-geth` execution client |\n| `reth` | `xlayer/reth/` | Reth execution client (upstream dependency) |\n| `xlayer-reth` | `~/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer-reth/` | X-Layer reth node ‚Äî custom logic built on reth's extensible architecture |\n| `xlayer-toolkit` | `xlayer/xlayer-toolkit/` | Miscellaneous scripts, local devnet launcher (`xlayer-toolkit/devnet/`) |\n\nFull paths:\n- `xlayer`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/`\n- `xlayer-reth`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer-reth/`\n- `optimism`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/optimism/`\n- `xlayer-toolkit`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/xlayer-toolkit/`\n\n---\n\n## X-Layer Architecture Overview\n\n### OP Stack Components (Go)\n\n- **`op-node`** ‚Äî derivation pipeline, consensus driver, L1 data retrieval, safe/finalized head tracking\n- **`op-conductor`** ‚Äî leader election and sequencer failover (Raft-based)\n- **`op-batcher`** ‚Äî batches L2 transactions and submits to L1 data availability\n- **`op-proposer`** ‚Äî submits L2 output roots to L1\n- **`op-challenger`** ‚Äî fault proof challenge agent\n- **`op-geth`** ‚Äî OP-modified Geth execution client (alternative EL to reth)\n\n### Execution Layer (Rust ‚Äî `xlayer-reth`)\n\nX-Layer uses reth as the primary execution client. `xlayer-reth` extends reth via its component architecture:\n\n- **Custom node builder** ‚Äî `XLayerNode` implementing reth's `NodeTypes` and component traits\n- **Payload building** ‚Äî custom `PayloadJobGenerator` and `PayloadBuilder` implementations\n- **RPC extensions** ‚Äî additional JSON-RPC namespaces and subscription APIs via `jsonrpsee`\n- **State management** ‚Äî `BundleState`, `CachedReads`, `StateProvider` overlays\n- **EVM execution** ‚Äî `revm` / `op-revm` with OP-specific transaction types\n- **Storage** ‚Äî MDBX-backed state trie, `reth-provider` abstractions\n- **Engine API** ‚Äî `engine_newPayloadV3/V4/V5`, `engine_forkchoiceUpdated` integration\n\n### Key Reth Abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | Crate | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `NodeTypes` | `reth-node-api` | Type-level node configuration (primitives, engine types, chain spec) |\n| `PayloadJobGenerator` | `reth-payload-builder` | Creates payload build jobs on FCU |\n| `BlockBuilder` | `reth-evm` | EVM execution pattern: `builder_for_next_block()` ‚Üí `execute_transaction()` ‚Üí `finish()` |\n| `StateProvider` | `reth-provider` | Read access to world state (accounts, storage, bytecode) |\n| `BundleState` | `revm` | Accumulated state changes with revert support |\n| `CachedReads` | `reth-revm` | In-memory overlay cache for state reads |\n| `StateRootProvider` | `reth-trie` | Incremental merkle trie updates for state root computation |\n| `TaskExecutor` | `reth-tasks` | Managed task spawning (`spawn`, `spawn_blocking`, `spawn_critical`) |\n\n---\n\n## Flashblocks Crate Map\n\n| Crate | Location | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `xlayer-builder` | `xlayer-reth/crates/builder/` | **Sequencer/builder** ‚Äî produces flashblocks, P2P propagation, WebSocket broadcast, payload building, engine pre-warm |\n| `reth-optimism-flashblocks` | `optimism/rust/op-reth/crates/flashblocks/` | **Execution/consumer** ‚Äî receives flashblocks via WS, EVM execution, builds pending state, consensus integration (`engine_newPayload` + FCU), sequence management, transaction caching |\n| `xlayer-flashblocks` | `xlayer-reth/crates/flashblocks/` | **RPC node** ‚Äî disk persistence, WebSocket relay, custom `eth_subscribe(\"flashblocks\")` subscription API with address filtering |\n\nFull paths:\n- `xlayer-builder`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer-reth/crates/builder/`\n- `reth-optimism-flashblocks`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer/optimism/rust/op-reth/crates/flashblocks/`\n- `xlayer-flashblocks`: `/Users/nivensie/dev/xlayer/op-stack/xlayer-reth/crates/flashblocks/`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n### 1. Builder / Sequencer (`xlayer-builder`)\n\nThe builder is embedded directly into the xlayer-reth node process. When `--flashblocks.enabled=true`, `FlashblocksServiceBuilder` replaces reth's default OP payload builder.\n\n**Key components:**\n- `OpPayloadBuilder` (`payload/flashblocks/payload.rs`) ‚Äî the core: runs the flashblocks build loop on a blocking thread. Schedules flashblocks via `FlashblockScheduler`, executes transactions via reth's EVM, calls `build_block()` per flashblock, sends results via channels.\n- `FlashblocksState` ‚Äî build state tracking: `flashblock_index`, `target_flashblock_count`, gas/DA limits, `last_flashblock_tx_index` for slicing new txs per flashblock.\n- `BlockPayloadJobGenerator` (`payload/generator.rs`) ‚Äî implements reth's `PayloadJobGenerator`. Maintains `CachedReads` via `on_new_state()` (populates cache from canonical chain execution outcomes). Creates `BlockPayloadJob` on FCU.\n- `BestFlashblocksTxs` (`best_txs.rs`) ‚Äî wraps pool iterator, skips already-committed txs via O(1) `HashSet\u003cTxHash\u003e` lookup, refreshes from pool on each flashblock boundary.\n- `FlashblockPayloadsCache` (`cache.rs`) ‚Äî `Arc\u003cMutex\u003cOption\u003cFlashblockPayloadsSequence\u003e\u003e\u003e` with atomic disk persistence. Enables follower replay via `get_flashblocks_sequence_txs(parent_hash)`.\n- `PayloadHandler` (`handler.rs`) ‚Äî routes payloads between builder, P2P, WebSocket, and engine events (`Events::BuiltPayload`).\n- `FlashblockScheduler` (`timing.rs`) ‚Äî computes wall-clock-aligned send times within block slots.\n- `WebSocketPublisher` (`wspub.rs`) ‚Äî broadcast flashblock deltas to WS subscribers via `tokio::sync::broadcast`.\n- P2P layer (`p2p/`) ‚Äî libp2p with protocol `/flashblocks/1.0.0`, TCP+noise+yamux, mDNS discovery, fan-out broadcast.\n\n**Module structure:**\n```\ncrates/builder/src/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ traits.rs                 # NodeBounds, PoolBounds, ClientBounds, PayloadTxsBounds\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ args/op.rs                # BuilderArgs, FlashblocksArgs, FlashblocksP2pArgs\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ metrics/builder.rs        # BuilderMetrics (~30+ metrics)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ p2p/{mod,behaviour,outgoing}.rs  # libp2p transport, behaviour, broadcast\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ payload/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ generator.rs          # BlockPayloadJobGenerator, BlockPayloadJob, CachedReads\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ context.rs            # OpPayloadBuilderCtx (EVM config, DA config)\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ builder_tx.rs         # BuilderTransactions trait\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ flashblocks/\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ payload.rs        # OpPayloadBuilder, FlashblocksState, build_block() ‚Äî THE CORE\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ service.rs        # FlashblocksServiceBuilder (wires everything)\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler.rs        # PayloadHandler (routing)\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cache.rs          # FlashblockPayloadsCache (persistence + replay)\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ timing.rs         # FlashblockScheduler\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ wspub.rs          # WebSocketPublisher\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ best_txs.rs       # BestFlashblocksTxs\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ p2p.rs            # Message enum, protocol definition\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config.rs         # FlashblocksConfig\n‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ context.rs        # FlashblockHandlerContext\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ tx/{signer,mock}.rs       # Signing, test utilities\n```\n\n### 2. Execution / Consumer (`reth-optimism-flashblocks`)\n\nThe upstream reth crate that RPC/follower nodes use to consume flashblocks from a sequencer's WebSocket stream and build local pending state.\n\n**Key components:**\n- `FlashBlockService` (`service.rs`) ‚Äî main event loop (`tokio::select!`): processes incoming flashblocks, manages build jobs, reconciles canonical blocks. Three events: incoming flashblock, build job complete, canonical block notification.\n- `SequenceManager` (`cache.rs`) ‚Äî ring buffer (3 slots) of recently completed sequences. Manages build ticket selection: canonical pending \u003e cached sequence \u003e speculative with pending parent.\n- `FlashBlockBuilder` (`worker.rs`) ‚Äî EVM execution on `spawn_blocking`. Uses reth's `BlockBuilder` pattern (`builder_for_next_block()` ‚Üí `execute_transaction()` ‚Üí `finish()`). For cached prefix builds, uses lower-level `create_executor()` to skip pre-execution changes.\n- `TransactionCache` (`tx_cache.rs`) ‚Äî caches cumulative `BundleState`, receipts, and execution metadata from previous flashblock builds within the same block. Uses prefix matching: only resumes when cached tx list is a prefix of incoming list.\n- `PendingStateRegistry` (`pending_state.rs`) ‚Äî bounded HashMap (64 entries) of `PendingBlockState`. Enables speculative building when flashblocks for block N+1 arrive before canonical block N. Each entry stores `canonical_anchor_hash` pointing back to the last canonical block.\n- `FlashBlockConsensusClient` (`consensus.rs`) ‚Äî submits `engine_newPayload` (when state_root is non-zero) and `engine_forkChoiceUpdated` using V5 API.\n- `FlashblockSequenceValidator` (`validation.rs`) ‚Äî classifies incoming flashblocks: `NextInSequence`, `FirstOfNextBlock`, `Duplicate`, `NonSequentialGap`, `InvalidNewBlockIndex`.\n- `ReorgDetector` / `CanonicalBlockReconciler` (`validation.rs`) ‚Äî detects reorgs via block fingerprints, determines reconciliation strategy: `CatchUp`, `HandleReorg`, `DepthLimitExceeded`, `Continue`.\n- WebSocket layer (`ws/`) ‚Äî `WsFlashBlockStream` connects to sequencer WS, decodes brotli/JSON via `FlashBlockDecoder`, auto-reconnects on failure.\n\n**Channel outputs:**\n- `PendingBlockRx\u003cN\u003e` (`watch`) ‚Äî latest pending block for `eth_getBlock(\"pending\")`\n- `FlashBlockCompleteSequenceRx` (`broadcast`) ‚Äî completed sequences for consensus submission\n- `FlashBlockRx` (`broadcast`) ‚Äî raw individual flashblocks for downstream subscription APIs\n- `InProgressFlashBlockRx` (`watch`) ‚Äî build-in-progress signaling\n\n**Epoch-based invalidation:** `state_epoch` counter increments on reorg/catch-up, invalidating all in-flight build results.\n\n**Module structure:**\n```\noptimism/rust/op-reth/crates/flashblocks/src/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lib.rs              # FlashblocksListeners, channel type aliases\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ service.rs          # FlashBlockService (main orchestrator)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cache.rs            # SequenceManager (ring buffer), BuildTicket, BuildCandidate\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ worker.rs           # FlashBlockBuilder (EVM execution)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tx_cache.rs         # TransactionCache (incremental prefix caching)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pending_state.rs    # PendingStateRegistry (speculative chaining)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ validation.rs       # Sequence validation, reorg detection, reconciliation\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ consensus.rs        # FlashBlockConsensusClient (engine API)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ payload.rs          # FlashBlock type alias, PendingFlashBlock\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sequence.rs         # FlashBlockPendingSequence, FlashBlockCompleteSequence\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ws/{mod,decoding,stream}.rs  # WebSocket stream, brotli/JSON decoding\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ test_utils.rs       # Test factories\n```\n\n### 3. RPC Node Extensions (`xlayer-flashblocks`)\n\nX-Layer custom logic for RPC nodes: persistence, WebSocket relay, and a rich subscription API.\n\n**Key components:**\n- `FlashblocksService` (`handler.rs`) ‚Äî spawns two critical tasks: disk persistence (writes each flashblock to `FlashblockPayloadsCache` + atomic file persist) and WebSocket relay (forwards flashblocks to `WebSocketPublisher`).\n- `FlashblocksPubSub` (`subscription.rs`) ‚Äî JSON-RPC `eth_subscribe(\"flashblocks\", filter)` with:\n  - Address filtering (sender, recipient, log-emitting addresses)\n  - Optional transaction enrichment (`tx_info: bool`)\n  - Optional receipt enrichment (`tx_receipt: bool`)\n  - Header streaming (`header_info: bool`)\n  - Transaction deduplication via `moka` LRU cache (10,000 entries)\n  - Configurable max subscribed addresses (default 1000)\n- Data types (`pubsub.rs`) ‚Äî `FlashblockSubscriptionKind`, `FlashblocksFilter`, `SubTxFilter`, `FlashblockStreamEvent` (tagged: `Header` | `Transaction`), `EnrichedTransaction`.\n\n**Wiring** (in `main.rs`): When NOT in sequencer mode, `FlashblocksService` is created with the `FlashBlockRx` from the upstream service. If `--xlayer.flashblocks-subscription` is enabled, `FlashblocksPubSub` replaces the standard `eth` pubsub module.\n\n**Module structure:**\n```\nxlayer-reth/crates/flashblocks/src/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lib.rs              # Re-exports\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler.rs          # FlashblocksService (persistence + WS relay)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pubsub.rs           # Subscription data types and filters\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ subscription.rs     # FlashblocksPubSub JSON-RPC API\n```\n\n---\n\n## Flashblocks Payload Model\n\nUses types from `op-alloy-rpc-types-engine`:\n\n- **`OpFlashblockPayload`** ‚Äî wire format for each flashblock delta:\n  - `payload_id: PayloadId`\n  - `index: u64` ‚Äî 0 = base/fallback, 1..N = incremental flashblocks\n  - `base: Option\u003cOpFlashblockPayloadBase\u003e` ‚Äî only at index 0: `parent_hash`, `fee_recipient`, `prev_randao`, `block_number`, `gas_limit`, `timestamp`, `extra_data`, `base_fee_per_gas`\n  - `diff: OpFlashblockPayloadDelta` ‚Äî `state_root`, `receipts_root`, `logs_bloom`, `gas_used`, `block_hash`, `transactions`, `withdrawals`, `withdrawals_root`, `blob_gas_used`\n  - `metadata: OpFlashblockPayloadMetadata` ‚Äî `receipts` (by tx hash), `new_account_balances`, `block_number`\n\n---\n\n## State Root Computation (Builder ‚Äî Three Modes)\n\n1. **Per-flashblock sync** (`disable_state_root = false`): Each flashblock calls `build_block(calculate_state_root=true)`. Inline: `state.merge_transitions()` ‚Üí `hashed_post_state()` ‚Üí `state_root_with_updates()`. Transition state is saved/restored for incremental builds.\n\n2. **Disabled per-flashblock** (`disable_state_root = true`): Flashblocks emit `state_root = B256::ZERO`. Only the fallback payload (index 0) computes state root.\n\n3. **Async on resolution** (`disable_async_calculate_state_root = false`): On `getPayload`, if best payload has zero state root, `resolve_zero_state_root` spawns on a blocking thread. Returns fallback payload immediately; async result pre-warms engine tree via `Events::BuiltPayload`.\n\n**Consumer side**: `FlashBlockConsensusClient` submits `engine_newPayload` only when `state_root != B256::ZERO`. FCU is always sent.\n\n**Rule**: State root MUST be computed before committing to the engine tree. Never delegate to an external EL.\n\n---\n\n## Performance Optimization Areas\n\n### 1. Sequencer Throughput (Gas/Second)\n\nGoal: Maximize gas processed per second on the sequencer.\n\nKey levers:\n- **Single canonical state** ‚Äî builder writes directly into the node's state provider, no cross-EL sync\n- **Engine cache hits** ‚Äî `Events::BuiltPayload` pre-warms engine tree so `engine_newPayload` is a cache hit, not re-execution\n- **`CachedReads` overlay** ‚Äî `on_new_state()` populates cache from canonical chain outcomes; EVM uses `cached_reads.as_db_mut(state_provider_db)`\n- **Transaction iteration** ‚Äî `BestFlashblocksTxs` skips committed txs via O(1) hash lookup, refreshes from pool per flashblock\n- **Flashblock scheduling** ‚Äî `FlashblockScheduler` aligns to wall-clock slots; configurable cadence (default 250ms), offset, end-buffer\n- **Follower catch-up** ‚Äî `FlashblockPayloadsCache` enables transaction replay on failover\n\nTarget: `engine_cache_hit_rate \u003e 99%`, `engine_newPayload` p50 \u003c 50ms, p95 \u003c 250ms\n\n### 2. Execution Speed (Reth Alignment)\n\nGoal: Transaction execution never blocks the async event loop.\n\nKey design:\n- **Blocking thread isolation** ‚Äî `OpPayloadBuilder::try_build()` runs on `spawn_blocking` (builder); `FlashBlockBuilder` uses `TaskExecutor::spawn_blocking()` (consumer)\n- **Reth EVM path** ‚Äî standard `evm.transact()` with `CachedReads` overlay (builder); `BlockBuilder` pattern with `execute_transaction()` (consumer)\n- **Incremental state** ‚Äî `BundleState` with `BundleRetention::Reverts` allows incremental flashblock builds; transition state snapshotted/restored between flashblocks (builder)\n- **Transaction prefix caching** ‚Äî `TransactionCache` provides warm `BundleState` prestate for prefix reuse within a block, avoiding redundant execution (consumer)\n- **DA-aware execution** ‚Äî per-tx DA size check (`OpDAConfig`) prevents DA overflow mid-flashblock\n\n### 3. State Trie \u0026 Merklization Speed (Reth Alignment)\n\nGoal: Minimize state root computation latency.\n\nKey design:\n- **`state_root_with_updates(hashed_state)`** ‚Äî uses `reth_trie` for incremental merkle trie updates via `StateRootProvider`\n- **`hashed_post_state(\u0026bundle_state)`** ‚Äî only hashes modified accounts/storage, not full state\n- **Transition save/restore** ‚Äî `merge_transitions` + restore avoids re-merging the full bundle on each flashblock\n- **Async resolution** ‚Äî state root computed on separate blocking thread while fallback payload returned immediately\n- **Engine pre-warm with trie data** ‚Äî async state root sends `BuiltPayload` event with `hashed_state` and `trie_updates` so engine tree applies them directly\n- **Consumer-side auto state root** ‚Äî triggered near expected final flashblock index (based on `block_time`)\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Reference\n\n### Flashblock